    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nickel plating is a process by which a metal (usually steel) is provided with a nickel layer. This forms a protective layer that protects against rust and other corrosion. There are two methods, a chemical (also called electroless or autocatalytic) nickel plating: where the object is immersed and autocatalytic chemical reactions take place in a bath, and galvanic or electrolytic nickel plating: where the object is hung in a bath and nickel plated by electrolysis, acting as a cathode.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
